verses.text_plain: And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, prophesy against the prophets of Israel that prophesy, and say thou unto them that prophesy out of their own hearts, Hear ye the word of the Lord;
verses.verse_html:
2Son of man, prophesy against the prophets of Israel that prophesy, and say thou unto them that prophesy out of their own hearts, Hear ye the word of the Lord; ▼
▼ that prophesy out…: Heb. that are prophets out of their own hearts

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that prophesy out…: Heb. that are prophets out of their own hearts
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that prophesy out…: Heb. that are prophets out of their own hearts

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord God; Woe unto the foolish prophets, that follow their own spirit, and have seen nothing!
verses.verse_html:
3Thus saith the Lord God; Woe unto the foolish prophets, that follow their own spirit, and have seen nothing! ▼
▼ follow: Heb. walk after
 , ▼
▼ and…: or, and things which they have not seen

footnotes.body_html: ▼ follow: Heb. walk after

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and…: or, and things which they have not seen
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and…: or, and things which they have not seen

verses.text_plain: O Israel, thy prophets are like the foxes in the deserts.
verses.verse_html: 4O Israel, thy prophets are like the foxes in the deserts.

verses.text_plain: Ye have not gone up into the gaps, neither made up the hedge for the house of Israel to stand in the battle in the day of the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
5Ye have not gone up into the gaps, neither made up the hedge for the house of Israel to stand in the battle in the day of the Lord. ▼
▼ gaps: or, breaches
 , ▼
▼ made…: Heb. hedged the hedge

footnotes.body_html: ▼ made…: Heb. hedged the hedge

verses.text_plain: They have seen vanity and lying divination, saying, The Lord saith: and the Lord hath not sent them: and they have made others to hope that they would confirm the word.
verses.verse_html: 6They have seen vanity and lying divination, saying, The Lord saith: and the Lord hath not sent them: and they have made others to hope that they would confirm the word.

verses.text_plain: Have ye not seen a vain vision, and have ye not spoken a lying divination, whereas ye say, The Lord saith it; albeit I have not spoken?
verses.verse_html: 7Have ye not seen a vain vision, and have ye not spoken a lying divination, whereas ye say, The Lord saith it; albeit I have not spoken?

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord God; Because ye have spoken vanity, and seen lies, therefore, behold, I am against you, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 8Therefore thus saith the Lord God; Because ye have spoken vanity, and seen lies, therefore, behold, I am against you, saith the Lord God.

verses.text_plain: And mine hand shall be upon the prophets that see vanity, and that divine lies: they shall not be in the assembly of my people, neither shall they be written in the writing of the house of Israel, neither shall they enter into the land of Israel; and ye shall know that I am the Lord God.
verses.verse_html:
9And mine hand shall be upon the prophets that see vanity, and that divine lies: they shall not be in the assembly of my people, neither shall they be written in the writing of the house of Israel, neither shall they enter into the land of Israel; and ye shall know that I am the Lord God. ▼
▼ assembly: or, secret, or, counsel

tokens.text: they shall not be in the assembly

footnotes.body_html: ▼ assembly: or, secret, or, counsel

verses.text_plain: Because, even because they have seduced my people, saying, Peace; and there was no peace; and one built up a wall, and, lo, others daubed it with untempered morter:
verses.verse_html:
10Because, even because they have seduced my people, saying, Peace; and there was no peace; and one built up a wall, and, lo, others daubed it with untempered morter: ▼
▼ a wall: or, a slight wall

tokens.text: Because, even because they have seduced

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a wall: or, a slight wall
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a wall: or, a slight wall

verses.text_plain: Say unto them which daub it with untempered morter, that it shall fall: there shall be an overflowing shower; and ye, O great hailstones, shall fall; and a stormy wind shall rend it.
verses.verse_html: 11Say unto them which daub it with untempered morter, that it shall fall: there shall be an overflowing shower; and ye, O great hailstones, shall fall; and a stormy wind shall rend it.

verses.text_plain: Lo, when the wall is fallen, shall it not be said unto you, Where is the daubing wherewith ye have daubed it?
verses.verse_html: 12Lo, when the wall is fallen, shall it not be said unto you, Where is the daubing wherewith ye have daubed it?

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord God; I will even rend it with a stormy wind in my fury; and there shall be an overflowing shower in mine anger, and great hailstones in my fury to consume it.
verses.verse_html: 13Therefore thus saith the Lord God; I will even rend it with a stormy wind in my fury; and there shall be an overflowing shower in mine anger, and great hailstones in my fury to consume it.

tokens.text: and there shall be an overflowing

verses.text_plain: So will I break down the wall that ye have daubed with untempered morter, and bring it down to the ground, so that the foundation thereof shall be discovered, and it shall fall, and ye shall be consumed in the midst thereof: and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 14So will I break down the wall that ye have daubed with untempered morter, and bring it down to the ground, so that the foundation thereof shall be discovered, and it shall fall, and ye shall be consumed in the midst thereof: and ye shall know that I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Thus will I accomplish my wrath upon the wall, and upon them that have daubed it with untempered morter, and will say unto you, The wall is no more, neither they that daubed it;
verses.verse_html: 15Thus will I accomplish my wrath upon the wall, and upon them that have daubed it with untempered morter, and will say unto you, The wall is no more, neither they that daubed it;

tokens.text: and upon them that have daubed

verses.text_plain: To wit, the prophets of Israel which prophesy concerning Jerusalem, and which see visions of peace for her, and there is no peace, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 16To wit, the prophets of Israel which prophesy concerning Jerusalem, and which see visions of peace for her, and there is no peace, saith the Lord God.

verses.text_plain: Likewise, thou son of man, set thy face against the daughters of thy people, which prophesy out of their own heart; and prophesy thou against them,
verses.verse_html: 17Likewise, thou son of man, set thy face against the daughters of thy people, which prophesy out of their own heart; and prophesy thou against them,

verses.text_plain: And say, Thus saith the Lord God; Woe to the women that sew pillows to all armholes, and make kerchiefs upon the head of every stature to hunt souls! Will ye hunt the souls of my people, and will ye save the souls alive that come unto you?
verses.verse_html:
18And say, Thus saith the Lord God; Woe to the women that sew pillows to all armholes, and make kerchiefs upon the head of every stature to hunt souls! Will ye hunt the souls of my people, and will ye save the souls alive that come unto you? ▼
▼ armholes: or, elbows

verses.text_plain: And will ye pollute me among my people for handfuls of barley and for pieces of bread, to slay the souls that should not die, and to save the souls alive that should not live, by your lying to my people that hear your lies?
verses.verse_html: 19And will ye pollute me among my people for handfuls of barley and for pieces of bread, to slay the souls that should not die, and to save the souls alive that should not live, by your lying to my people that hear your lies?

verses.text_plain: Wherefore thus saith the Lord God; Behold, I am against your pillows, wherewith ye there hunt the souls to make them fly, and I will tear them from your arms, and will let the souls go, even the souls that ye hunt to make them fly.
verses.verse_html:
20Wherefore thus saith the Lord God; Behold, I am against your pillows, wherewith ye there hunt the souls to make them fly, and I will tear them from your arms, and will let the souls go, even the souls that ye hunt to make them fly. ▼
▼ to make…: or, into gardens

footnotes.body_html: ▼ to make…: or, into gardens

verses.text_plain: Your kerchiefs also will I tear, and deliver my people out of your hand, and they shall be no more in your hand to be hunted; and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 21Your kerchiefs also will I tear, and deliver my people out of your hand, and they shall be no more in your hand to be hunted; and ye shall know that I am the Lord.

tokens.text: and they shall be no more in your hand

verses.text_plain: Because with lies ye have made the heart of the righteous sad, whom I have not made sad; and strengthened the hands of the wicked, that he should not return from his wicked way, by promising him life:
verses.verse_html:
22Because with lies ye have made the heart of the righteous sad, whom I have not made sad; and strengthened the hands of the wicked, that he should not return from his wicked way, by promising him life: ▼
▼ by…: or, that I should save his life: Heb. by quickening him

tokens.text: whom I have not made sad

footnotes.body_text: ▼ by…: or, that I should save his life: Heb. by quickening him
footnotes.body_html: ▼ by…: or, that I should save his life: Heb. by quickening him

verses.text_plain: Therefore ye shall see no more vanity, nor divine divinations: for I will deliver my people out of your hand: and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 23Therefore ye shall see no more vanity, nor divine divinations: for I will deliver my people out of your hand: and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
